This Python script calculates the Body Mass Index (BMI) based on weight and height inputs.

Description
The Body Mass Index (BMI) is a value derived from an individual's weight and height and is commonly used to categorize a person's weight status.

Prerequisites
Before running the script, ensure you have Python installed on your system.

Usage
1-Run the script.
2-Enter your weight in kilograms when prompted.
3-Enter your height in meters when prompted.
The script will display your calculated BMI.

Interpretation of BMI
The BMI values typically fall into categories such as underweight, normal weight, overweight,
and obese. You can interpret the BMI value according to standard ranges provided by health organizations.
